Clone or download this repository.
Open the project in Android Studio.
Ensure your project is synced with Gradle.
Run the app on an Android device or emulator.


How it Works
User Input: The user inputs the text they want to convert into a QR code.
Generate QR Code: Upon clicking the "Generate QR Code" button, the app encodes the text into a QR code.
Display QR Code: The generated QR code is displayed in an ImageView.
Share QR Code: Once the QR code is generated, the "Share QR Code" button becomes visible, allowing users to share the code with others.
Technologies Used
Android SDK (Java)
Material Design components (e.g., MaterialButton, TextInputLayout)
QR Code generation (Using a QR code generation library such as ZXing)
